R=C3=A9sum=C3=A9 de la th=C3=A8se:=20
---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
---------------------------------------=20
Les progr=C3=A8s conjugu=C3=A9s de l'algorithmique et des infrastructures i=
nformatiques permettent aujourd'hui d'extraire de plus en plus d'informatio=
ns pertinentes et utiles des donn=C3=A9es issues de r=C3=A9seaux de capteur=
s ou de services web. Ces plateformes de traitement de donn=C3=A9es "massiv=
es" sont confront=C3=A9es =C3=A0 plusieurs probl=C3=A8mes. Un probl=C3=A8me=
 de r=C3=A9partition des donn=C3=A9es: le stockage de ces grandes quantit=
=C3=A9s de donn=C3=A9es impose l'agr=C3=A9gation de la capacit=C3=A9 de sto=
ckage de plusieurs machines. De l=C3=A0 d=C3=A9coule une seconde probl=C3=
=A9matique: les traitements =C3=A0 effectuer sur ces donn=C3=A9es doivent =
=C3=AAtre =C3=A0 leur tour r=C3=A9partis efficacement de mani=C3=A8re =C3=
=A0 ne surcharger ni les r=C3=A9seaux, ni les machines.=20

Le travail de recherche men=C3=A9 dans cette th=C3=A8se consiste =C3=A0 d=
=C3=A9velopper de nouveaux algorithmes de r=C3=A9partition de charge pour l=
es syst=C3=A8mes logiciels de traitement de donn=C3=A9es massives. Le premi=
er algorithme mis au point, nomm=C3=A9 "WACA" (Workload and Cache Aware Alg=
orithm) am=C3=A9liore le temps d'ex=C3=A9cution des traitements en se basan=
t sur des r=C3=A9sum=C3=A9s des contenus stock=C3=A9s sur les machines. Le =
second algorithme appel=C3=A9 "CAWA" (Cost Aware Algorithm) tire partie de =
l'information de co=C3=BBt disponible dans les plateformes de type "Cloud C=
omputing" en =C3=A9tudiant l'historique d'ex=C3=A9cution des services.=20

L'=C3=A9valuation de ces algorithmes a n=C3=A9cessit=C3=A9 le d=C3=A9velopp=
ement d'un simulateur d'infrastructures de "Cloud" nomm=C3=A9 Simizer, afin=
 de permettre leur test avant le d=C3=A9ploiement en conditions r=C3=A9elle=
s. Ce d=C3=A9ploiement peut se faire de mani=C3=A8re transparente gr=C3=A2c=
e au syst=C3=A8me de distribution et de surveillance de service web nomm=C3=
=A9 "Cloudizer", d=C3=A9velopp=C3=A9 aussi dans le cadre de cette th=C3=A8s=
e, qui a servi =C3=A0 l'=C3=A9valuation des algorithmes sur l'Elastic Compu=
te Cloud d'Amazon.=20

Ces travaux s'inscrivent dans le cadre du projet de plateforme de traitemen=
t de donn=C3=A9es Multim=C3=A9dia for Machine to Machine (MCube). Ce projet=
 requiert une infrastructure logicielle adapt=C3=A9e au stockage et au trai=
tement d'une grande quantit=C3=A9 de photos et de sons, issus de divers r=
=C3=A9seaux de capteurs. La sp=C3=A9cificit=C3=A9 des traitements utilis=C3=
=A9s dans ce projet a n=C3=A9cessit=C3=A9 le d=C3=A9veloppement d'un servic=
e d'adaptation automatis=C3=A9 des programmes vers leur environnement d'ex=
=C3=A9cution.=20
---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
---------------------------------------=20

En anglais=20
---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
---------------------------------------=20
Nowadays, progresses in algorithmics and computing infrastructures allow to=
 extract more and more adequate and useful information from sensor networks=
 or web services data. These big data computing platforms have to face seve=
ral challenges. A data partitioning issue; storage of large volumes imposes=
 aggregating several machines capacity. From this problem arises a second i=
ssue: to compute these data, tasks must be distributed efficiently in order=
 to avoid overloading networks and machines capacities.=20

The research work carried in this thesis consists in developping new load b=
alancing algorithms for big data computing software. The first designed alg=
orithm, named WACA (Workload And Cache Aware algorithm) enhances computing =
latency by using summaries for locating data in the system. The second algo=
rithm, named CAWA for "Cost AWare Algorithm", takes advantage of cost infor=
mation available on so-called "Cloud Computing" platforms by studying servi=
ces execution history.=20

Performance evaluation of these algorithms required designing a Cloud Infra=
structure simulator named "Simizer", to allow testing prior to real setting=
 deployment. This deployement can be carried out transparently thanks to a =
web service monitoring and distribution framework called "Cloudizer", also =
developped during this thesis work and was used to assess these algorithms =
on the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud platform.=20

These works are set in the context of data computing platform project calle=
d "Multimedia for Machine to Machine" (MCube). This project requires a soft=
ware infrastructure fit to store and compute a large volume of pictures and=
 sounds, collected from sensors. The specifics of the data computing progra=
ms used in this project required the development of an automated execution =
environement adaptation service.=20
---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
---------------------------------------=20

Mots-cl=C3=A9s:=20
R=C3=A9partition de charge, Cloud, Donn=C3=A9es Massives, Filtres de Bloom=
